After (if the logo links to the homepage):
<img src="logo.png" alt="COC Base Layouts - Go to homepage">

After (if purely decorative and nearby text provides the same information):
<img src="logo.png" alt="">

Note: An empty alt="" is appropriate ONLY when the image is purely decorative AND the information is provided elsewhere. For logos that convey brand identity or serve as navigation, always provide descriptive alt text.","aiPriority":7},{"issueId":"9713c6e0-433f-4e34-8e19-f01deeb0d764","aiExplanation":"This link contains only an icon element with no accessible text, making it impossible for screen reader users to understand the link's purpose. When a screen reader encounters this link, it may announce nothing, 'link', or potentially an unhelpful icon font character. Keyboard-only users who navigate by tabbing through links will also have no context about where this link leads. This creates a frustrating guessing game for users who cannot see the visual icon.","aiFixSuggestion":"Add accessible text to the link using one of these approaches:

